# Cloudflare Pages routing.
# Blog posts have no per-slug file — serve the blog SPA shell for any /blog/<slug>
# so the clean URL is preserved (SEO + sharing) and app.js reads the slug from
# location.pathname.
#
# IMPORTANT: the rewrite target must be the EXTENSIONLESS clean URL (/blog), not
# /blog.html. Pages auto-redirects any *.html path to its clean URL, so a 200
# rewrite to /blog.html gets bounced with a 308 to /blog — which drops the slug
# and lands every post back on the blog index. Rewriting to /blog avoids that.
/blog/*   /blog   200

# Open invite links: /join/<open_token> serves the RSVP shell (extensionless
# target for the same 308 reason; rsvp.js reads the token from the path).
/join/*   /rsvp   200
